 • On Tuesday evening Queens Bottle Store in Hendrina was robbed by a group of armed men. Robbers pistol whipped a Chinese woman against the head and made off with cash, cigarettes and a cellphone. • On Wednesday five armed men robbed Foschini’s in OR Tambo Street. Robbers fled in a white KIA in the direction of the Old Witbank Road (R555). Also read: Armed suspects hit again • On Thursday morning Incredible Connection in the Middelburg Mall was robbed. Five armed robbers entered the business armed with three duvet covers. They targeted laptops and fled via the emergency exit of the mall, dragging their loot behind them. • Also on Thursday, police and security officers from Mid Alarms managed to trap a group of suspects inside the roof of the building that hosts Club Malibu next to the Old Pick ’n Pay building. It is suspected that they planned on robbing California Lounge Entertainment Centre. Police arrested at least six suspects.  Armed suspects hit again Taxi passengers injured in collision No mercy for mentally and physically disabled   • Save our standby number (072 248 3855) and send us a WhatsApp message with the words “Add me” to be added to our broadcast list. • Like us on Facebook, follow us on Twitter and Instagram. • Subscribe to our YouTube channel. • Click on the link to subscribe to our bi-weekly newsletter via email. Contact our news room on our 24 hr standby number 072 248 3855, or send a mail to our editor tobie@mobserver.co.za